spanGrp.span: The village is looking very good.
The joy is coming back today.
I will tell a story about
the Saratoga man and the Bushfowl man
he was the Sagara's story man
it is coming from the ancestors.
nzo.ne ŋaf.yən bä.ʔin ʔa.ne tri.ka.si ya.tri.kwath
They told that story to my father, to Mbäi.
My father told me this story
He is quoting what his father was saying to him from here onwards.
the saratoga fishlings were inside here.
Those two were fighting right here.
Over there at Kanathér was the stone.
when they cut this one (the stone).
wəm ma.ne səf.rä.rəm bo.ba wa.zi ne.ba kwa.ri.ta.kwə.rəm
It was this stone which went across from one side to the opposite side (of the river)."
This way, I will start this story now in the morning.
just like I was saying before
from the sagara, the Morehead sagara ...
It was my Mayawa story man
There used to be a rock/stone there
(from) the opposite side of the river to
naf sa.fak fur bo.ba zran thum.gəth.kwə.rəm
He was feeding the saratoga children there in the swamp
He was feeding the bushfowls over there
They (2) each had a trapping place.
"wä" has scope over "enta" (two) > "really two each have a trap"; if the form was "entanmewä" the emphasis would be on the possessive > "really both have a trap together"
sa.fak menz ka.be ʔa.ne ma.ne swa.rä.rəm
He put it down over there by the stone ...
na.fa.ne fä gu.fi.yar we zəf.rä.rəm fi
where he had his fishing basket, but...
He was eating only small ones.
where the Sanḡara story man was staying
was eating the really big ones.
At the time when he walked ...
The cockatoo bird was sitting above
He said: "Oh, the man is coming."
Okay, as for the fish that is there
for what is the ground oven here?"
I have cut the yamcake yesterday."
"This is the ground oven from yesterday."
but he was tricking him badly.
ni.ma.nzo no.mai swa.fi.yo.kwə.rəm ʔe no.mai no.mai no.mai
He did this to him again and again.
My friend here is tricking me.
because the bones are lying there
wa.tik nä kay.ʔə zə.ba kwa tö.na.fa wi.yak
one day I will walk from here, from the high ground."
wa.tik tö.na.fa ma.ne yan.yak nä kay.ʔə ka.na.thər
Then, one day, he was coming from the high ground to Kanathér.
He set off from Téferisam and.....
wa.tik sa.fak fur ʔa.ne fof yay.ʔam.gwa
he was surprised about his saratoga fishlings
he killed those saratoga fishlings in the swamp
bä.ne.ma ko.fä ka.ro ʔa.ne fof yay.ʔam.gwa fof
yamnḡési = surprise shock, yamnḡésikaf wamnzér, tauri nzä kwayamḡwér
because he was already surprised about the fish oven
sazirako = past; threw it to him; yirzési
he threw the saratoga fishling down
bu.ka.ren ʔa.ne fof bä sa.fak ʔem.gəth.kwa
you fed the saratoga fish at your place"
the pulled each other. the hit each other
and hit each other, and hit each other
wa.ti sa.fak menz ma.ne yan.ra tə.fri.sam
okay, as for the Saratoga man ...
tə.fri.sa.men fä fof fai.ko.re ʔef.nza ʔef.nza ʔef.nza ne.zä we nä.bi sre.fa.fo
he killed those bushfowls over there in Téférisam. In return he also got one.
ya nzo.ne bä ni.ma thu.wa.fi.yo.kwə.rəm be.rä
"You are doing this to my things ...
wəm ʔa.ne fof ka.na.thren bä ma.ne yə.thən
Those stones which lay in Kanathér ...
they stick out a little bit
abia first heard it, but then denied the ergative on ausi; farkési = set off; *ausif, they say "ausi fóf"
The Saratoga man said to his wife:
because the Bushfowl man was cutting them
The stones were about to disappear
the Saratoga man went across at Théfén
and he went down in Garaita
the Bushfowl man who came ... the story man
thoraksi; he arrived in yari (story place in masu)
ka.tan ni.ma zə.bo zəf zway.thək fof
wa.tik ze.na ʔa.ne.ma ma.ne ʔe.rən fof
Okay, that is why today the two ...
the Sanḡaras in nḡaraita and the Mayawas
yarisi = give; sisters are exchanged between nḡarait and masu, but not to marry them. they are given in order to
from here they give them as exchange women
and in return they give them to us.
verb; thuwaythékérén (2things come to an end), thuwaythék (3s things come to an end). ntsraythékérén, ntsraithékérném, tsena kwa waythék, wanéythék waythéko, naythékérén (2), naythék (3)
